	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">coinheaven wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">it looks like from the pictures you wired it like this:<br /><br />bent up pins 1,2,24,31,32<br />wired pin 1 to pin 16<br />wired pin 24 to pin 22<br />wired pin 2 to hole 24<br />wired pin 31 and pin 32 to pin 30<br /><br />can you confirm if this is correct?</div>
<br />OK, I just got the cart. Yup, this is all correct.
<br />
<br />The only thing missing is pin 30 (A17), which was also bent to be connected to the mapping hardware. I don't know what the size of the PRG-ROM of your game is, but whatever address lines are not used should be connected to GND (like I did with pin 1).
<br />
<br />Also, keep in mind that this cart was made for an AT29C040 Flash ROM, as you can see in the pictures. If your chip is different, just look at the datasheets of both chips to see how they differ from each other and make the proper adjustments.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
