<br />
<br />the prg is 128 kb, so i am using a 27c010 eprom chip.  it looks like they are very similar, except for pins 1, 30,31,32:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.datasheetcatalog.com/datasheets_pdf/2/7/C/0/27C040.shtml">http://www.datasheetcatalog.com/datashe ... C040.shtml</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />EPROM 27C010/27C1001 128KBytes (32pin):
<br />
<br />               ---_---
<br />        VPP - |01   32| - VCC
<br />        A16 - |02   31| - PGM
<br />        A15 - |03   30| - NC
<br />        A12 - |04   29| - A14
<br />        A7  - |05   28| - A13
<br />        A6  - |06   27| - A8
<br />        A5  - |07   26| - A9
<br />        A4  - |08   25| - A11
<br />        A3  - |09   24| - OE
<br />        A2  - |10   23| - A10
<br />        A1  - |11   22| - CE
<br />        A0  - |12   21| - D7
<br />        D0  - |13   20| - D6
<br />        D1  - |14   19| - D5
<br />        D2  - |15   18| - D4
<br />        GND - |16   17| - D3
<br />               -------
<br />
<br />what is PGM, NC, OE and CE?  I know what they stand for (No connect, Output enable, Chip enable, but dont understand them when it comes to rewiring.  like why do you wire A16 to OE?

		

